'''[[Alle]]''', '''[[Allah]]''', '''Ilaah''' iyo '''Rabbi''' ({{lang-ar|الله}} {{lang-it|Dio}} {{lang-en|God}} Ge'ez: እግዚአብሔር) ({{IPAc-en|lang|pron|ˈ|æ|l|ə}} or {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɑː|l|ə}};<ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/allah "Allah"]. ''Random House Webster's Unabridged Dictionary''.</ref> {{lang-ar|الله}} {{transl|ar|ALA|''Allāh''}}, {{IPA-ar|ʔalˤˈlˤɑːh|IPA|Ar-allah.ogg}}) (''[[Arabic definite article|al]] ilāh'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/empires/islam/faithgod.html |title=God |work=Islam: Empire of Faith |publisher=PBS|accessdate=18 December 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327034958/http://www.pbs.org/empires/islam/faithgod.html|archivedate=2014-03-27}}</ref><ref>"Islam iyo Christianity", ''Encyclopedia of Christianity'' (2001): Arabic-speaking Christians and Jews also refer to God as ''Allāh''.</ref><ref>{{cite encyclopedia | title=Allah | encyclopedia=Encyclopaedia of Islam Online | author=L. Gardet | accessdate=2 May 2007}}</ref> waa awooda guud ee maamula [[koon]]ka iyo wixii ku dhex jira ee [[dad]]ka, [[jin]]ka, [[malag|malaa'igta]], [[shaydaan]]ka iyo wixii soo raaca leh. 
Sida ku xusan [[diin]]ta [[Islaam]]ka, Ilaahay waa [[aqoon]]-badane, [[awood]]-badane, meel walba jooga, wax kasta maqla, wax kasta arka, wax kasta og, kan ugu wanaagsan, siduu doono yeele, waligiis soo noolaa, waligiis noolaan doona, waxba aan dhalin, asaga la dhalin.
